Sentencas: The oxygen transports were investigated at the O-2/cathode/Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2(YSZ)
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: interfaces for solid oxide fuel cells(SOFCs).
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: The isotope oxygen exchange technique (O-16/O-18 exchange) and secondary ion mass spectrometry (SIMS) analysis were adopted to determine the active sites for oxygen adsorption, surface oxygen exchange, and incorporation of oxygen around the O-2/cathode/YSZ triple phase boundaries (TPBs).
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: The cathode surfaces were active for oxygen adsorption and surface oxygen exchange than the free surfaces of YSZ, which suggested the higher activity on the cathode surfaces.
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: The active sites for oxygen incorporation were determined with mesh shape cathodes (La0.9Sr0.1MnO3 and Au) and porous cathode (Ag).
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: The SIMS images clearly determined the active sites for oxygen incorporation on YSZ surfaces: the cathode/YSZ interfaces were active for oxygen incorporation as well as TPB in the La0.9Sr0.1MnO3-mesh and the Ag-porous cathodes.
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: On the other hand, only the TPB lines were active for oxygen incorporation in the Au-mesh.
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: The expansion of active sites from the TPB was considered on the basis of the SIMS images.
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices

Sentencas: The bulk diffusion of oxygen was also investigated at the LaMnO3 film/YSZ samples.
Titulo: Oxygen transport at the hetero interfaces of electrochemical ceramic devices
